      "id": "PopularPost354671",
      "post_content": "I run this in my Oona Mill EDH deck, and played it turn 1 in a casual six player game. Everyone was too distracted by a [Purphoros, God of the Forge](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Purphoros, God of the Forge) swarm deck very quickly dealing commander damage to everyone to worry about me, and thanks to that deck my counters were going up almost on everyone's turn.  \n  \nTurn 7 I dropped [Traumatize](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Traumatize) onto the Purphorous player, making them mill 42 cards, lose 84 life and making me gain 84 life. Suddenly, I'm the target.  \n  \nTurn 8, I cast [Mind Grind](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mind Grind) for 6, killing all but one player, who eventually succumbs to life lost after casting a spell and me countering with [Psychic Strike](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Psychic Strike).  \n  \nI never expect to win like this again, but boy was it amazing.",
      "posted_by": "Acorntail",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost354671\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">I run this in my Oona Mill EDH deck, and played it turn 1 in a casual six player game. Everyone was too distracted by a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Purphoros, God of the Forge\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Purphoros, God of the Forge\">Purphoros, God of the Forge</a> swarm deck very quickly dealing commander damage to everyone to worry about me, and thanks to that deck my counters were going up almost on everyone's turn.<br/><br/>Turn 7 I dropped <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Traumatize\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Traumatize\">Traumatize</a> onto the Purphorous player, making them mill 42 cards, lose 84 life and making me gain 84 life. Suddenly, I'm the target.<br/><br/>Turn 8, I cast <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Mind Grind\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mind Grind\">Mind Grind</a> for 6, killing all but one player, who eventually succumbs to life lost after casting a spell and me countering with <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Psychic Strike\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Psychic Strike\">Psychic Strike</a>.<br/><br/>I never expect to win like this again, but boy was it amazing.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '354671'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"post